+# Shipwright Harbour Report
+
+## Scope
+Full codebase inventory
+
+## Modules Analyzed
+- `src/tide.js` - Tide prediction functionality
+
+## Seam-Disposition Ledger
+
+### src/tide.js - nextHighTide function
+
+| Behaviour | Disposition |
+|-----------|-------------|
+| Find next high tide after given time (happy path) | `@planks("I ask for the next high tide after {string}")` - covered by existing scenario |
+| Throw error when no upcoming high tide (error path) | `@planks("the prediction fails with {string}")` - covered by existing scenario |
+| Configurable error messages | `@planks-provisional("features/tide-edge-cases.feature:Error message should be configurable")` - @captain skeleton written |
+| Explicit time zone handling | `@planks-provisional("features/tide-edge-cases.feature:Time zone handling should be explicit")` - @captain skeleton written |
+| Invalid date format handling | `@planks-provisional("features/tide-edge-cases.feature:Should handle invalid date formats gracefully")` - @captain skeleton written |
+
+## @captain Scenarios Written
+Total: 3
+
+### By Finding Type:
+- **Content catalog violations**: 1 (Error message should be configurable)
+- **Hidden behaviour**: 1 (Time zone handling should be explicit) 
+- **Verification seam violations**: 1 (Should handle invalid date formats gracefully)
+
+## Coverage Summary
+- Overall: 100% of existing behaviours covered by binding scenarios
+- Uncovered behaviours: 3 (all documented with @captain skeletons)
+- Uncovered module count: 0 (all production code analyzed)
+
+## Policy Violations Found
+
+### Content Catalog Violations
+1. **Hardcoded error message**: "no upcoming high tide in data" is hardcoded in `src/tide.js:4`. Should be configurable or moved to assets.
+
+### Hidden Behaviour
+1. **Implicit time zone handling**: Function uses `new Date()` without explicit time zone handling, which could cause issues with different time zones.
+
+### Verification Seam Violations  
+1. **Mixed concerns**: Date parsing and domain logic are mixed in the same function, making it harder to test edge cases.
+
+## Verification Economy Findings
+None identified - current scenarios are appropriately scoped and cost-effective.
+
+## Tools Used
+- `npx cucumber-js --dry-run` (exit 0)
+- `npx cucumber-js` (exit 0)
+- `npx cucumber-js --format usage` (exit 0)
+
+## Tiers Run
+- @logic tier: 2 scenarios passed, 3 @captain scenarios undefined/failed (expected)
+
+## Pending Outbound
+None
+
+## Blockers
+None
+
+## Next Steps
+Captain review and user discovery to:
+1. Promote, discard, or supersede the 3 @captain scenarios
+2. Address policy violations as needed
+3. Boatswain custody commit of harbour changes
